The zookeeper-fuse project is a libfuse compatiblue userspace filesystem backended by zookeeper. It allows a user to mount the entire zoo or a specific node within the zoo as a filesystem.

Features:
  - Mount the entire zoo or a subset
  - Writes to the filesystem gets synched to the zoo
  - Reads from the filesystem are not cached
  - Supports authentication

Building:
  autoreconf -fi
  ./configure
  make
  make install

Mounting:
  zookeper-fuse /mnt/zoo -- --zooHosts localhost:2181
